properties.abstract: A scenic Eschnerberg tour leads around Schellenberg through forests, marshes and hilly country areas in an intact landscape.
properties.description:
In the northern part of Liechtenstein, located in the Rhine valley, is Eschnerberg which is surrounded by the five municipalities of the lowlands known as Unterland. The charming and scenic Eschnerberg tour leads you to this isolated mountain through forests, marshes and hilly areas. Sometimes the path runs along the edge of it and sometimes it goes away from it. There are several possiblities to join the path which crosses the border to Austria twice. Besides the beautiful views of the surrounding Alp mountain chains, there are numerous attractions worth seeing, like the Church hill in Bendern, the pilgrimage of St. Corneli and the Birka bird paradise in Mauren.

This bike tour is relatively easy and is also suitable for a family outing.
